    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Soft, yellowish-white wood of the species Populus tremula, native to Europe and Asia. It is easy to work, but weak, prone to warping, and produces a disagreeable odor when wet. The lightweight, spongy wood is generally used for matches, excelsior, fruit crates, and paper pulp.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
